songs.title: Thirsty Lamps
songs.lyrics:
Thirsty lamps are stealing my cancer
But green giraffes will fight them away
Upside down I don’t have the answer
Cause I keep drifting further away

West side whale say he wants a listen
Skinless cat with ribbon is gay
Thirsty lamps are stealing my cancer
But green giraffes will fight them away

I know you don’t think that I’m better at all
I’m here to catch you any time that you fall
It’s not as easy as they all make it seem
I’m here to pull you into one of my dreams

Dirty boys on carpeted sunrise
Special black in eyes of the moon
Why am I addicted to cancer
Cause it locks me inside my room

I know you don’t think that I’m better at all
I’m here to catch you any time that you fall
It’s not as easy as they all make it seem
I’m here to pull you into one of my dreams

It’s not as easy as they all make it seem

I’m here to catch you any time that you fall
It’s not as easy as they all make it seem

I know I know I know
I know I know I know

I know you don’t think that I’m better at all
